  "text": "We next used dynamic contrast enhanced magnetic resonance (DCE-MRI) to determine whether inhibition of LMP1 expression by DZ1 had any effect on tumor microvascular permeability (Fig. 6C) . The parameter of K trans derived from DCE-MRI has been widely used to evaluate anti-tumor drugs [CITATION_1] . We compared the K trans values of DZ1-, CDN-or saline-treated mice after radiotherapy and found significant differences between (Fig. 6D) . However, significant differences between the DZ1 and control groups were not observed in nonirradiated animals. These results indicated that DZ1 inhibited LMP1 expression in mice, which might promote IR-mediated changes in tumor vasculature.",
